          "date": "2011-08-31 20:52:43.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "TT-148 test: workaround for negative time shifts",
        "message": "TT-148 test: workaround for negative time shifts\n\nTry to workaround negative test timestamps being seen in Maloo.\nIt appears that the negative time shifts are always even multiples\nof 7h (= -25200s) so try to compensate for this when printing out\ntest durations and the test completion summary line.\n\nThe fix doesn't hard-code 25200s offset, since I suspect this is\nsomehow related to confusion by the client/host between UTC and\nPDT (where the test clusters are hosted) and this offset will change\nas daylight savings time changes.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I95e6cc35986167dec86190d4f50d8b43dc9fabd3\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
